{"id":"2004.13986","submitter":"Matthieu Dussaule","authors":"Matthieu Dussaule (LMJL)","title":"Local limit theorems in relatively hyperbolic groups II : the\n  non-spectrally degenerate case","comments":null,"journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.DS math.GR math.PR","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  This is the second of a series of two papers dealing with local limit\ntheorems in relatively hyperbolic groups. In this second paper, we restrict our\nattention to non-spectrally degenerate random walks and we prove precise\nasymptotics of the probability $p_n(e, e)$ of going back to the origin at time\n$n$. We combine techniques adapted from thermodynamic formalism with the rough\nestimates of the Green function given by the first paper to show that $p_n(e,\ne) \\sim CR^{-n} n^{-3/2}$ , where $R$ is the spectral radius of the random\nwalk. This generalizes results of W. Woess for free products and results of\nGou{\\\"e}zel for hyperbolic groups.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 29 Apr 2020 07:00:41 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-04-30"}
